      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "a7130f5e7cf75169",
        "text": "xxx posted:\nI am convinced by now that this issue of covering all use cases is not specific to my work on Leibniz. I think the fundamental issue is supporting different phases of the knowledge lifecycle, from playing with new ideas to presenting proven knowledge in a way that others can build on (school/university textbooks, Wikipedia, ...). Another dimension is individual vs. collective exploration and refinement of knowledge. The various knowledge management tools I am aware of all have their zone of application in this space. But none deals with the transition between phases in the lifecycle, nor with the ping-pong motion between individual work and work in different collectives."
      },
      "after": "33aed3aae8779357",
      "date": 1676752974820
