        "text": "xxx posted in (Matrix federated wiki)[https://matrix.to/#/!ORfrUEFeWFcHAMLFLr:matrix.org/$1676728924314496hwjvj:matrix.org]:\nI am convinced by now that this issue of covering all use cases is not specific to my work on Leibniz. I think the fundamental issue is supporting different phases of the knowledge lifecycle, from playing with new ideas to presenting proven knowledge in a way that others can build on (school/university textbooks, Wikipedia, ...). Another dimension is individual vs. collective exploration and refinement of knowledge. The various knowledge management tools I am aware of all have their zone of application in this space. But none deals with the transition between phases in the lifecycle, nor with the ping-pong motion between individual work and work in different collectives."
